It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves training and evaluating neural networks. Additionally, since the paper mentions the use of state-of-the-art RNN models, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of sentential embeddings, which could potentially involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
